caption: Just Perfect! So glad we got to sit inside. The place is immaculate and the decor/ambiance was exactly what we needed. Then you add the service and the Pizza - Yes Perfection. I had the Donna Amatrice and it was absolutely amazing. Can’t wait to go back for more. Priced family friendly each of my boys had different Pizza and enjoyed every bite. Dessert - Tiramisu & Tartufo Gelato and  Cappucinos. Loved every minute. We went home happy 😊
Had a fantastic lunch. Highly recommend.

A low fodmap dream restaurant! The gluten free crust is cornmeal based, the tomato sauce is just tomatoes, and all ingredients are listed on the menu. Besides that, the food is excellent. It can get a bit noisy inside, but the food and service more than makes up for it.
This restaurant has indoor & outdoor dining, the food is absolutely delicious & the staff here is courteous & friendly. Reccomend dining in or ordering out here.
Delicious 😋

Delicious pizza! Ran into this cute shop on the way to the Brooklyn Heights Promenade and decided to grab a pie and walk over to the overpass. I highly recommend doing it! Beautiful views of the city + a great meal. The pizza tasted very fresh.

Why: Three tacos for only $10?! Packed with birria meat with onions, cilantro, salsa, and lime. The soft shell had a surprisingly perfect crisp to it and it was u-shaped allowing more ingredients and less mess. Definitely try dipping the tacos in the Consomé for added flavor, then sip or drink the soup.  Notes: I walk by this food truck all the time from the 4,5,6 Subway and usually there's a lot of people in the area because it's in front of Shake Shack and other department stores so I bypass it to limit crowding; however, I went on a Saturday right before the lunch crowd and I am forever changed! I hope they stay in that location long-term because I'll be coming back for sure. I want to try their other items like Quesadilla, Mulita and Tostada. Simple menu, affordable and delicious eats, and seemed clean.

One of the beat Brooklyn style pizza’s I’ve had in the city! The meatballs are also quite delicious; the sauce they use on their pizza and meatballs is what truly makes it delicious. The service was also very quick and we got our pizza very fast. Though it is a bit more on the pricey side, I think it was well worth it. I’d definitely recommend to any pizza lover looking for a great pizzeria in Brooklyn!

I’ve been to New York two times over the past two years, and each time I’ve stopped at Dellarocco’s. First time wasn’t planned, second time I made sure it was my first stop. When I realized I was gluten intolerant, pizza was the first thing I missed. After having Dellarocco’s I realized I never before had better tasting pizza, even when I was eating gluten. I’m just sad I didn’t have it again before I left. Oh, they also had amazing salads. That dish with the tomato, basil, and mozzarella, was OUT OF THIS WORLD. Service might have been a bit slow if I remember correctly, but then again both times I was starving and ready to eat the table. Can’t wait to come back.

By the way, our friend wasn’t keen on having pizza for dinner because “pizza is a snack not a meal”. The pizza is excellent. Our friend walked away amazed and happy.  It’s located in the heart of the downtown area off Montague on Hicks street. The location is awesome because you are just steps away from the promenade. At least for now the promenade is still in tact. They’re talking about building now roadway there which would be sad. In any event, back to the restaurant.  The atmosphere is basic but highly welcoming. The service staff is really attentive and there are so many pizza options.  And the gluten free pies were really great. I don’t think you could tell the difference.  The arugula white pic is the one I had. My boyfriend had the margarita. And our friend had a regular crust with sausage.  We shared a bottle of Barbera. It was heavier than a Pinot noir but lighter than a cab.  This place had the total package for us.

This is my favorite Italian style pizza in all of NYC. 3 months ago I was in Italy and the second I took a bite of this pizza, I was brought right back. The atmosphere is romantic, intimate, calm. The service is gentle, kind, quick. The food *THE FOOD* well, the pizza was delicious. Specifically the Tartufata. Truffle cream? Speck? I mean, this is the real deal. The wine I had was very good at $9 a glass. I will be coming back, for sure! Wish I'd found it sooner!!! Must, must go!
Cozy ambiance and good food. I recommend you start with a drink called Mr. Rocco. Delicious and smooth! Great service! Liked the pizza. Good salad dressing.

Very good pizza place about 5 blocks away from work. It’s always worth the walk for lunch. The pizza’s are 12” personals and are always made available immediately. The place itself is pretty open concept and it’s always clean, not too crowded. The staff is pretty fast and polite and the pizzas are delicious. I would recommend the margarita and the sausage pie.
Excellent pizza.

Pizza is delicious, undoubtedly the best in Brooklyn. If you have a sweet tooth, you need to try the Nutella pizza!

Food: Started with the meatball appetizer.  3 meatballs for $11.  Skip this and order another pizza. As for their crust, it's chewy, the outer crust is crispy but the center of the pizza is soggy. That's the style. Decor/Vibe: Simple but cozy. I'm a fan.  I also like the bar and the number of local taps they have is great. Service was friendly but not particularly attentive. Overall, not bad, a bit pricey, but cozy and enjoyable.
Great pizzas.
Best pizza in Brooklyn Heights, if not Brooklyn. Thin crust, fresh ingredients, nice atmosphere.

My first time back East from Hawaii since 1981 was an experience I have shared with all of my friends. The Calzone was the best I have ever consumed.
